values.description:
The bash script used to install Gazebo dependencies tries to install OSRF packages, like sdformat, libsimbody, ignition-math and ignition-transport.
In a clean Ubuntu 14.04  installation we need to add OSRF pre-compiled repository.

This tutorial doesn't give the dependencies to install sdformat and ignition libraries from source... (Some modification in [dependencies_archive.sh](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/release-tools/src/e0c595d74f45f4607ddd8fa14dadf0caf2c8a1b1/jenkins-scripts/lib/dependencies_archive.sh?at=default&fileviewer=file-view-default) are required )
values.title: Add OSRF repository to install pre-compiled pkgs

summary.raw:
The bash script used to install Gazebo dependencies tries to install OSRF packages, like sdformat, libsimbody, ignition-math and ignition-transport.
In a clean Ubuntu 14.04  installation we need to add OSRF pre-compiled repository.

This tutorial doesn't give the dependencies to install sdformat and ignition libraries from source... (Some modification in [dependencies_archive.sh](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/release-tools/src/e0c595d74f45f4607ddd8fa14dadf0caf2c8a1b1/jenkins-scripts/lib/dependencies_archive.sh?at=default&fileviewer=file-view-default) are required )
summary.html:
The bash script used to install Gazebo dependencies tries to install OSRF packages, like sdformat, libsimbody, ignition-math and ignition-transport. In a clean Ubuntu 14.04 installation we need to add OSRF pre-compiled repository.

This tutorial doesn't give the dependencies to install sdformat and ignition libraries from source... (Some modification in dependencies_archive.sh are required )
